comments.body:
Personally, I haven't seen a good solution to this problem.  Options including loading `Model` with an optional declaration of every possible property, or cobbling together something like 

```ts
interface Model1 {
    P1: string;
    P2: number;
    P3?: never;
}
interface Model2 {
    P1?:never;
    P2: number;
    P3: boolean;
}

declare const _model: Model1 | Model2;
```

`_model` will have `P1` and `P3` optional and `P2` required and the declaration accurately conveys that the caller should probably assert one of the individual model types.  The downside is that all the declarations have to stay in sync (there might be something clever you can do with index signatures, but I didn't find it while experimenting).

